-- Essilor International Agrees to Buy 50% of Nasdaq-Traded Shamir Optical
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-10-15T06:23:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/essilor-international-agrees-to-buy-50-of-nasdaq-traded-shamir-optical.html
Essilor International SA has signed
an agreement to buy 50 percent of Shamir Optical Industry Ltd.,
Essilor said in a statement on its website.  Shamir Optical, based in Israel and traded on Nasdaq, had
2009 sales of $142 million, Essilor said. Kibbutz Shamir will
hold the other 50 percent of Shamir Optical, according to the
statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Whitehouse at 
 dwhitehouse1@bloomberg.net  